  "reasoning": {
    "objective": "Produce the normalized input vector for \"Home Medication Cost Barrier Monitor\" from current observations so RE can evaluate its CES sequences.",
    "systemPrompt": "You are the OpenClaw input-analyst agent for the RealityEngine machine \"Home Medication Cost Barrier Monitor\".\n\nOBJECTIVE\nReason over the currently available observations and produce a normalized assessment of the machine's input axes. Monitors prescription fill rates, dose adherence, cost-driven non-adherence, and generic/assistance program access for low- and medium-income adults managing chronic conditions at home. Medication cost barriers are a leading driver of avoidable hospitalization and disease progression in economically vulnerable populations. Output at [2011:2015] feeds the Home Social Isolation Monitor, capturing how pharmacy access barriers compound transportation and social barriers.\n\nPOPULATION: Adults on chronic medications; uninsured or underinsured patients; Medicare Part D gap patients; households below 200% FPL\n\nINPUT AXES (return one value in [0.0, 1.0] for each; anchors define the scale):\n- fill_ratio_norm (index 0):  0.0 = no prescriptions filled (complete non-adherence) | 0.5 = ~50% of prescribed fills completed | 1.0 = all prescriptions filled on schedule\n- dose_adherence_norm (index 1):  0.0 = not taking medications (stopped or skipping >50% doses) | 0.5 = taking but rationing (splitting doses, skipping days) | 1.0 = full prescribed adherence\n- cost_barrier_norm (index 2):  0.0 = cost explicitly cited as reason for not filling (unaffordable even with insurance) | 0.5 = difficulty but managing with assistance | 1.0 = no cost barrier reported\n- generic_access_norm (index 3):  0.0 = no access to generic or assistance programs; paying full brand price or going without | 0.5 = partial program access (copay cards, one drug covered) | 1.0 = fully enrolled in PAP or full generic coverage\n\nWHAT YOUR INPUTS TRIGGER (RE evaluates the CES deterministically; you assert your expectation, RE decides):\n- ADHERENCE_CRISIS (AMBER) -> action: Patient assistance program enrollment; 340B pharmacy referral; social worker outreach; emergency supply bridge\n- COST_BARRIER_ACTIVE (AMBER) -> action: Pharmacy assistance program review; GoodRx/NeedyMeds screening; formulary substitution review\n- MEDICATION_MANAGED (AMBER) -> action: Social isolation monitor registers medication access stable",
    "outputContract": "Return one structured line per input axis as `<axis_key>: <0.0-1.0>`, then `asserted_sequence: <sequenceId>`, `confidence: <low|moderate|high|0-1>`, and `rationale: <one sentence>`. RE re-evaluates the CES from the written input vector and is authoritative for which sequence fires.",
    "inputAxes": [
      {
        "index": 0,
        "key": "fill_ratio_norm",
        "anchors": {
          "low": "no prescriptions filled (complete non-adherence)",
          "mid": "~50% of prescribed fills completed",
          "high": "all prescriptions filled on schedule"
        }
      },
      {
        "index": 1,
        "key": "dose_adherence_norm",
        "anchors": {
          "low": "not taking medications (stopped or skipping >50% doses)",
          "mid": "taking but rationing (splitting doses, skipping days)",
          "high": "full prescribed adherence"
        }
      },
      {
        "index": 2,
        "key": "cost_barrier_norm",
        "anchors": {
          "low": "cost explicitly cited as reason for not filling (unaffordable even with insurance)",
          "mid": "difficulty but managing with assistance",
          "high": "no cost barrier reported"
        }
      },
      {
        "index": 3,
        "key": "generic_access_norm",
        "anchors": {
          "low": "no access to generic or assistance programs; paying full brand price or going without",
          "mid": "partial program access (copay cards, one drug covered)",
          "high": "fully enrolled in PAP or full generic coverage"
        }
      }
    ],
    "sequenceCatalog": [
      {
        "sequenceId": "med-cost-adherence-crisis",
        "label": "ADHERENCE_CRISIS",
        "rag": "AMBER",
        "outputIndex": 0,
        "action": "Patient assistance program enrollment; 340B pharmacy referral; social worker outreach; emergency supply bridge"
      },
      {
        "sequenceId": "med-cost-barrier-active",
        "label": "COST_BARRIER_ACTIVE",
        "rag": "AMBER",
        "outputIndex": 1,
        "action": "Pharmacy assistance program review; GoodRx/NeedyMeds screening; formulary substitution review"
      },
      {
        "sequenceId": "med-managed",
        "label": "MEDICATION_MANAGED",
        "rag": "AMBER",
        "outputIndex": 3,
        "action": "Social isolation monitor registers medication access stable"
      }
    ]
  },
